h3. Summary:
When setting [LDAP integration|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Connecting+to+an+LDAP+Directory], it's possible to [enable nested groups|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Managing+Nested+Groups]. It's also possible to write [User Object Filters|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Connecting+to+an+LDAP+Directory#ConnectingtoanLDAPDirectory-UserSchemaSettings] to restrict the synchronization scope.

h3. Current behavior:

When setting an *User Object Filters* as the following example:
{code}
(&(objectCategory=Person)(sAMAccountName=*)(memberOf=CN=jira-users,OU=jira,DC=company,DC=local))
{code}

Only the direct members of *jira-users* group are pulled in after the synchronization, members of nested groups that are associated to the parent group are not picked up during the synchronization.

h3. Expected behavior:

